<?php
/* Security release? */
$notes['security'] = true;

/* Mailing list release notes. */
$notes['changes'] = <<<ML
The Horde Team is pleased to announce the final release of the Horde Groupware
version 5.1.5.

Horde Groupware is a free, enterprise ready, browser based collaboration
suite. Users can manage and share calendars, contacts, tasks and notes with the
standards compliant components from the Horde Project.

For upgrading instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/groupware/docs/UPGRADING

For detailed installation and configuration instructions, please see
http://www.horde.org/apps/groupware/docs/INSTALL

The major changes compared to the Horde Groupware version 5.1.4 are:

Security fixes:
    * Fixed broken encryption of session data.
    * Don't leak database authentication/connection information in exception
      messages.
    * Stricter LDAP parameter check to detect empty passwords.

General changes:
    * Updated Danish, Hungarian, Japanese, Korean, and Spanish translations.
    * Bugfixes and improvements.
ML;

$notes['name'] = 'Horde Groupware';
$notes['list'] = 'horde';
return $notes;
